The paper deals with the complexity of solving combinatorial games, specifically variations of the QBF problem. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of reductions, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The analysis of game rules and conditions also relates to topics in logic (cs.LO) and game theory (cs.GT).
